olive oil
1 carrot
1 stalk celery
½ Onion
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
1 packet tomato paste
20 g butter (for the sauce)
1 tsp plain flour
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
¾ cup milk
¼ cup water
1 packet Baby Leaves
30 g butter (for the pastry)
1 packet filo pastry

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Grate carrot.
• Finely chop celery and onion (see ingredients).

Little cooks: Under adult supervision, older kids can help grate the carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

• Add carrot, celery and onion to the pan, stirring, until softened, 4-6 minutes.
• Add classic roast seasoning, tomato paste, the butter(for the sauce) and plain flour, then cook, stirring until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add garlic & herb seasoning, the milk and the water and cook, stirring, until reduced, 2-3 minutes.

• Remove pan from heat, add baby leaves and stir to combine.
• Transfer pork filling to a baking dish.

• In a small microwave-safe bowl, add the butter (for the pastry). Microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Lightly scrunch each sheet of filo pastry and place on top of the pork filling to completely cover. Gently brush melted butter over to coat.
• Bake pie until pastry is golden, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can take the lead by scrunching the filo pastry!

• Divide pork and hidden veggie filo pie between plates to serve. Enjoy!